  "original_title": "\u2019\u0ba8\u0bbe\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0b95\u0bc1\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0bb1\u0bb5\u0bbe\u0bb3\u0bbf \u0b85\u0bb2\u0bcd\u0bb2\u2019",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "'I am not guilty'",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Former President Maithripala Sirisena has said in the House that he is not going to accept that he is guilty of the Easter Sunday attack and that he rejects the allegations related to it.",
        "Addressing the Parliament yesterday (5), in the report of the Presidential Commission on the Manusha Nanayakkara Sunday attack incident,",
        "The former President said this while responding to the comment made by the opposition leader Sajith Premadasa about how he had held a meeting with the accused person and how he was going to cooperate with him.",
        "Since 6 months ago, the Sri Lanka Freedom Party had discussed with the President and demanded the formation of an all-party government. It was also said that we are ready to take responsibility in that government.",
        "Meanwhile, if the case is to be prosecuted according to the report of the commission regarding the Easter Sunday attack, the Attorney General's Department can do so. There are already 8 human rights cases pending against me in the High Court. Similarly, there are up to 400 cases filed by the affected parties against me, the former Prime Minister and the Defense Secretary.",
        "In this case, I set up a commission regarding the Easter Sunday attack. They said they thought they knew the attack was going to happen in that suggestion.",
        "According to this, the commission should file a case. But no case was filed in this regard. Therefore, I am not going to admit that I am guilty anywhere. He said he rejects it."
      ],
